title: Dyer's Record Book (USA), 1871
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Printer's sample book with formulas for dyestuffs. Contains 114 samples in various designs including paisley.

tombstone.epitaph: Dyer's Record Book (USA), 1871; Manufactured by Old Pacific Print Works ; cardboard, paper, printed wool samples; H x W x D (closed): 33.7 x 21.5 x 1.8 cm (13 1/4 x 8 7/16 x 11/16 in.); Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts; 1945-55-8
